images.title: Coasting along Big Sur
images.caption: Spotting whales from Big Sur
images.desc: In late winter and early spring here on the US Pacific coast, thousands of grey whales, many with calves in tow, swim past California's Big Sur as they migrate from the warm waters of Mexico to their summer feeding grounds in the Bering Sea.
